  "body": "#System information\r\nGeth version: 1.9.0\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : n/a\r\n\r\nCounter.Close() will cause a segmentation error when the limit is set to a small value and the log is printed concurrently.\r\n\r\nWhen I add the lock, it will run normally.\r\n```go\r\n        h := StreamHandler(counter, formatter)\r\n        mu := sync.Mutex{}\r\n\treturn FuncHandler(func(r *Record) error {\r\n\t\tmu.Lock()\r\n\t\tdefer mu.Unlock()\r\n\t\tif counter.count > limit {\r\n\t\t\tcounter.Close()\r\n\t\t\tcounter.w = nil\r\n\t\t}\r\n```",
